# Working conventions for this workspace — {DOMAIN} OS

You operate the {DOMAIN} operating system. Your job is not just to file things — it is to keep the
system **current and compounding**. Act autonomously on the rules below. (AGENTS.md is a symlink to
this file.)

## Auto-manage loop (run on new input, without being asked)
1. Place the raw file in its correct home, dated YYYY-MM-DD.
2. Read it.
3. Extract reusable value into `knowledge-base/` (insights / faqs / decisions).
4. Scan the related {ENTITY}/{PIPELINE} folder; read its README; reconcile.
5. Update everything affected in the SAME turn: entity README dashboards, `{PIPELINE}/_board.md`,
   `operating-system/dashboard.html`, metrics. (never-stale rule)
6. Move folders to match reality (stage changes); update the external system of record if any.
7. Mine for compounding assets (templates, proof, FAQs).
8. Report what changed.

Confirm before inventing {DOMAIN} facts; otherwise just do the routine filing and summarize.

## Never stale (state management is your job)
If you touched the project, leave it consistent. After any change, ask which other files now disagree
with reality and update them all. The `{DOMAIN}-janitor` skill is the backstop and runs on a schedule.

## Compound learning (get smarter every session)
Every session deposits at least one durable learning (a decision, a canonical answer, an insight, or
an improved template/skill). Search `knowledge-base/` before solving anything — never twice.

## Anything done more than once becomes a skill
When a task repeats, author `skills/{name}/SKILL.md` and repackage the plugin (see `skills/_packaging/`).

## Filing decision tree
1. Reusable instrument (template/script/checklist)? -> `library/`
2. Repeatable task/capability? -> `skills/`
3. Reusable answer/insight/decision/SOP? -> `knowledge-base/`
4. Flowing item not yet done? -> `{PIPELINE}/`
5. Tied to a core entity? -> `{ENTITY}/`
6. Outcome/proof? -> `proof/`
7. Raw/idea/draft/published? -> `content/`
8. Canon/source/spec? -> `reference/`
9. Legal/finance/metrics? -> `business-ops/`

## Don't
- Don't duplicate canon; reference `reference/`.
- Don't invent facts the user must own — mark inferred items "draft — confirm".
- Don't leave the system stale after input — run the loop.
